                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">391.1164/144: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-27T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 27, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Your 164, July 16, 9 a.m. and 171, July 19, 11 a.m. The Department commends
                    your efforts on behalf of Presbyterian Board and congratulates you on the
                    successful outcome of your negotiations to obtain settlement from the Iranian
                    Government.</p>
                <p>Boyce cabled negotiators July 22 “Answering cable 19th, Board accepts terms
                    outlined”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
